com.camerontec.catalys.application.marketdata

Class MDEntryStore

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.application.marketdata.MDStoreBase
      • com.camerontec.catalys.application.marketdata.MDEntryStore
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IMarketDataEntryStore, ISetValueStore

    public class MDEntryStore
extends MDStoreBase
implements ISetValueStore, IMarketDataEntryStore
    Store of market data, populated by the various setValue methods and the setInstrumentValues method. The data can be iterated over returning the ITagValues representing this data in a Market Data FIX message.

    The FIX representation returned by the iterator is different depending on whether the incremental flag is set. If set, the FIX fields are those used in a FIX Market Data Incremental Refresh message (MsgType = X), otherwise the fields are those used in a FIX Market Data Snapshot message (MsgType = W).

    Author:
    John Cameron

      • MDEntryStore

        public MDEntryStore(IInstrumentUpdateInfo updateInfo,
                    boolean incremental,
                    int iteratorType)
        Create a store associated with the given instrument info.

        The iterator for the store will return fields corresponding to an incremental FIX market data message if incremental is true, otherwise a snapshot FIX market data message.

        Parameters:
        updateInfo - Instrument update info associated with store.
        incremental - True if iterator should return fields for an incremental FIX marketdata message, otherwise snapshot.
        iteratorType - iterator type

        public StandardTagValue getNextStoreTagValue(char mdEntryType)
        Retrieves the next StandardTagValue available for storing data associated with given mdEntryType.

        Note: Side effect is that it assumes that the returned store is now used and it will increment the number of used tag values for this mdEntryType.

        Parameters:
        mdEntryType - MDEntryTYpe associated with data
        Returns:

      • setValue

        public void setValue(IFixFieldInfo fieldInfo,
                     IMarketDataValue value)
        Description copied from interface: ISetValueStore
        Set the value on the message corresponding to the FIX field defined in the given fixFieldInfo.

        Note that fixFieldInfo includes, among other things, the FIX tag value and possible MDEntryType associated with this field.

        Only variable values of the reusable message should be set using this method. Any value set by this method is automatically assumed to be variable (ie cannot be reused).

        If mdEntryType is '\0', then the value is not part of an MDEntry - but is the field with the given FIX tag, outside the MDEntries part of the message.

        Specified by:
        setValue in interface ISetValueStore
        Parameters:
        fieldInfo - Defines the FIX field associated with the given value.
        value - Value for this field.
